Interface ResourceConsumerA

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConnectionType, DeviceType, ModifierLevel, ResourceBundles, ResourceType, ResourceTypeModifierLevel, SignalType, TaskType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConnectionTypeImpl, DeviceTypeImpl, ResourceBundlesImpl, ResourceConsumerAImpl, ResourceTypeImpl, ResourceTypeModifierLevelImpl, SignalTypeImpl, TaskTypeImpl

    public interface ResourceConsumerA
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Resource Consumer A'. Abstract base class of a resource consuming element. Instances are functions, devices, subdevices or resources itself.

    The following features are supported:

    • Required Resources
    • Consumed Groups
    See Also:
    LibraryPackage.getResourceConsumerA()

    • Method Detail

      • getRequiredResources

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Resource> getRequiredResources()
        Returns the value of the 'Required Resources' containment reference list. The list contents are of type Resource. The required resource a resource consumer will consume when mapped to a resource provider. The required resources are, however, a wishlist. The precise resource consumption of a resource consumer is specified in the capabilities layer
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Required Resources' containment reference list.
        See Also:
        LibraryPackage.getResourceConsumerA_RequiredResources()

      • getConsumedGroups

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<ResourceGroup> getConsumedGroups()
        Returns the value of the 'Consumed Groups' containment reference list. The list contents are of type ResourceGroup. Resource groups organize the resources of the resource consumer in groups, e.g. galvanic groups of I/Os, etc.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Consumed Groups' containment reference list.
        See Also:
        LibraryPackage.getResourceConsumerA_ConsumedGroups()
